# Day 9 – CloudWatch Agent Setup

## Goal
Install and configure the Amazon CloudWatch Agent on an EC2 Ubuntu instance to collect metrics and logs.

## Steps Taken
1. Launched EC2 Ubuntu instance.
2. Connected via SSH.
3. Installed CloudWatch Agent package.
4. Edited configuration file (`amazon-cloudwatch-agent.toml`):
   - Added disk and memory metrics.
   - Attempted to add `/var/log/syslog` log collection.
5. Restarted agent and checked status:
   ```bash
   sudo systemctl status amazon-cloudwatch-agent
   sudo journalctl -u amazon-cloudwatch-agent -n 20
6. Attached IAM role with CloudWatchAgentServerPolicy.
